In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 2015 as National Adoption Month in the United States. He acknowledges the selflessness of adoptive families and expresses gratitude for their dedication to providing a safe and loving home for children in need. The article highlights the significant number of children in foster care and emphasizes the importance of finding permanent homes for them. President Obama also mentions various initiatives and policies aimed at supporting adoptive parents, such as expanded workplace flexibility and the Adoption Tax Credit. He also notes the Intercountry Adoption Universal Accreditation Act, which enforces legal standards for adoption service providers. Additionally, the article mentions the Supreme Court's ruling on marriage equality, stating that it will benefit same-sex couples and provide more opportunities for children in foster care to find loving families. The article concludes by encouraging Americans to observe National Adoption Month by finding permanent families for children in need and supporting adoptive families.